orageversion/manager.go** file defines the `Manager` interface (line 54) that records which resources need storage version updates and provides methods for:\n\n- `AddResourceInfo()` - Records resources whose StorageVersions need updates\n- `UpdateStorageVersions()` - Updates StorageVersions of recorded resources in etcd\n- `PendingUpdate()` - Checks if a resource's StorageVersion update is pending\n- `LastUpdateError()` - Returns the last error for a resource's update\n- `Completed()` - Returns whether all updates are complete\n\nThe `defaultManager` struct (line 70) implements this interface and maintains resource-to-StorageVersion mappings.\n\n## ResourceEncodingConfig Interface\n\nThe **staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/server/storage/resource_encoding_config.go** file defines:\n\n1. **ResourceEncodingConfig interface** (line 28) - Determines which GroupVersion is used for etcd storage:\n   - `StorageEncodingFor()` - Returns the serialization format (GroupVersion) for storing a resource\n   - `InMemoryEncodingFor()` - Returns the in-memory representation encoding\n\n2. **DefaultResourceEncodingConfig struct** (line 42) - Implements the interface with:\n   - `resources` map storing overriding encoding configs per GroupResource\n   - `SetResourceEncoding()` - Sets custom storage encoding for specific resources\n   - `StorageEncodingFor()` - Returns the external storage encoding version\n   - `InMemoryEncodingFor()` - Returns the internal storage encoding version\n\nThis config allows explicit mapping of v1beta1 resources to their v1 equivalents for etcd storage while maintaining backward compatibility for decoding multiple versions.\n\n## Integration Pattern\n\nThe pattern followed across all storage providers is:\n1. Each API group has a `RESTStorageProvider` (or `StorageProvider`) struct in its rest package\n2. The provider implements separate `v1Storage()`, `v1beta1Storage()`, and optionally `v1alpha1Storage()` methods\n3. `NewRESTStorage()` calls each version's method and populates `VersionedResourcesStorageMap` in the `APIGroupInfo`\n4. The `ResourceEncodingConfig` determines which version is actually used for etcd persistence\n5. The `StorageVersion` Manager tracks which versions are being used and updates the StorageVersion API objects accordingly\n\nThis architecture enables Kubernetes to serve multiple API versions (v1, v1beta1, v1alpha1, etc.) while using a single underlying storage version in etcd, with automatic conversion between formats as needed."
